                <head>125. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On July 19 the Department responded to telegram 171 from Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_WTK1">Wright</persName> in Jordan, which requested U.S.
                    assistance to allow the Arab Union Government to destroy the insurrection and
                    restore the legitimate status in Iraq. (Department of State, Central Files,
                    787.00/7–1958) The Department responded in telegram 203, July 19, printed in
                        <ref target="frus1958-60v11#pg_344">volume XI, pages 344</ref>–<ref
                        target="frus1958-60v11#pg_345">345</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
